stylometry: A simulation model is a computer model that imitates a real-life situation. this model is like other mathematical models, but it incorporates uncertainty in one or more of the input variables. When we run a simulation, we allow these random input variables to take on various values, and we keep track of any resulting output varialbes of interest. in this way, we are able to see how the outputs vary witht the varying inputs. A great benefit of this enables us to answer the what-if questions without changing or building a pysical system. this will help us by not having to spend money on changing or building a new way oh doing things.
